#: ../../faq.rst:928
# a1e4e123de9b42af98629de68f354b2e
msgid "How do I get |app| to use my HTTP proxy?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../faq.rst:930
# 98e6b25d4eeb4279a4e547c7a032f3a6
msgid "By default, |app| uses whatever proxy settings are set in your OS. Sometimes these are incorrect, for example, on windows if you don't use Internet Explorer then the proxy settings may not be up to date. You can tell |app| to use a particular proxy server by setting the http_proxy environment variable. The format of the variable is: http://username:password@servername you should ask your network admin to give you the correct value for this variable. Note that |app| only supports HTTP proxies not SOCKS proxies. You can see the current proxies used by |app| in Preferences->Miscellaneous."
msgstr ""

